# Bundle Test Conventions

## General

- `declare(strict_types=1)` in test files too
- Structure: `tests/Unit/`, `tests/Integration/`, `tests/Functional/` when applicable; for small bundles a lighter layout is fine (e.g. only `tests/Integration/`)
- PHPUnit testsuite name in `phpunit.xml.dist` can stay generic (e.g. "Unit") even if test classes live under `Integration/`
- Use `nyholm/symfony-bundle-test` with `TestKernel` for integration tests

## Minimum Required Tests

- Bundle boots without error
- All services are correctly registered and wired
- Configuration validation (required keys, default values, custom values)
- Twig prepend (paths registered, globals set) when applicable

## Exception Handler Cleanup

Symfony's TestKernel registers exception handlers. Always restore them in `tearDown()` to avoid PHPUnit "risky test" warnings:

```php
protected function tearDown(): void
{
    parent::tearDown();
    \restore_exception_handler();
}
```

## Integration Test Template

```php
use Nyholm\BundleTest\TestKernel;
use Symfony\Bundle\FrameworkBundle\Test\KernelTestCase;
use Symfony\Component\HttpKernel\KernelInterface;

final class BundleBootTest extends KernelTestCase
{
    protected function tearDown(): void
    {
        parent::tearDown();
        \restore_exception_handler();
    }

    protected static function getKernelClass(): string
    {
        return TestKernel::class;
    }

    protected static function createKernel(array $options = []): KernelInterface
    {
        /** @var TestKernel $kernel */
        $kernel = parent::createKernel($options);
        $kernel->addTestBundle(VendorNameBundle::class);
        $kernel->addTestConfig(static function ($container): void {
            $container->loadFromExtension('framework', ['test' => true]);
        });
        $kernel->handleOptions($options);

        return $kernel;
    }
}
```

Key patterns:
- `/** @var TestKernel $kernel */` for PHPStan compatibility
- `static function` closures in `addTestConfig()` (no `$this` binding)
- Register TwigBundle when testing Twig integration (globals, paths)
- `$kernel->getContainer()->get('test.service_container')->get('twig')` for Twig access in custom-booted kernels

## PHPUnit Configuration

- `failOnRisky="true"` in `phpunit.xml.dist` (enforce clean tests)
- Always pair with `restore_exception_handler()` in `tearDown()` to pass risky check

## Live Components

Test with `InteractsWithLiveComponents` trait in `KernelTestCase`:

```php
use Symfony\UX\LiveComponent\Test\InteractsWithLiveComponents;

$component = $this->createLiveComponent(name: SearchLive::class, data: ['query' => 'test']);
$component->call('loadMore');
self::assertSame(2, $component->component()->page);
```

## Twig Components

Test rendering via Twig render assertions or by checking rendered HTML output.

## After Every Change

Run `make test` then `make infection` to verify coverage and mutation score.
